The Daily News' coverage of LaGuardia's violent encounter with Hagan. 
  
Der Angriff (The Attack), Goebbels fact-free voice box, demanded that the half-Jew mayor of the the world metropolis of Jewry be locked up. It called him a Jewish bug and a cheap Jewish apostle with his cheap Jewish brain. 
 
Once and for all we want it understood that we will not tolerate insults to the Fuhrer, the paper whined. We Germans demand that in dealing with us courtesy be employed, to which we have been accustomed for 2,000 years. 
 
The German-American Conference of Greater New York chimed in, declaring without irony that LaGuardias remarks about the obvious German persecution of religious and racial minorities breeds race hatred and ill-feeling among our citizens of different racial extractions. 
 
The Nazi press cheered when LaGuardia got slugged at City Hall. Der Angriff growled that it showed how well the half-Jew is liked by his closest fellow-citizens. 
 
LaGuardia got his black eye 41 days after Kristallnacht, when 1,000 Jews were killed and 30,000 were arrested in 24 hours. Soon after getting his shiner, LaGuardia threw another jab while accepting a check to help resettle Jewish refugees. Conditions in Germany are the shame and horror of civilization, he declared. 
 A clipping from a News story about Hagan.   
Hagan, the slugger, proved to be Irish, not German. He was charged with assault and was due in court 10 days later. But he was diagnosed with delusions of persecution, and LaGuardia graciously waved criminal charges. 
 
He is a very sick boy, and I feel very sorry for him, the mayor said. 
 
Hagan was transferred to a Long Island hospital for long-term treatment and slipped out of the public eye. 
 
His larger enemy did not. 
 
LaGuardias fight with Hitler grew more personal when the family of his sister, Gemma LaGuardia Gluck, who had married a Hungarian Jew, was confined to concentration camps after the 1944 Nazi invasion of Budapest. By then, the rest of America had come around to LaGuardias point of view. 
 
Gemma Gluck survived, but her husband and son-in-law perished. 
 
She later said she had demanded an explanation during her arrest. A brown shirt replied, It is enough that you are LaGuardias sister. 
